=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">The wildest aspect of the wildest deal of =
2024 has to be the
handshake agreement between <strong>Shari Redstone</strong>, the owner of P=
aramount Global, and <strong>David Ellison</strong>, the Oracle heir who se=
arched his father=E2=80=99s couch cushions for most of the $8 billion he sp=
ent to buy it from her. Ellison, as I reported more than a year ago now, pr=
omised from the onset of talks that he wouldn=E2=80=99t turn around and fli=
p the storied film and television company to another bidder. Yes, he will l=
ikely cleave off some lesser assets=E2=80=94a dying cable network here, a
streaming joint venture there, $2 billion in cost cuts planned overall=E2=
=80=94but that=E2=80=99s just triage.=C2=A0=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;m=
argin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">In th=
e great race to consolidate Hollywood for the digital age=E2=80=94a movemen=
t that, in 2024, led far too many industry moguls to embarrass themselves b=
y publicly cheerleading for M&amp;A activity that would wipe out entire stu=
dios and decimate the creative output they claim to care about=E2=80=94Reds=
tone liked
Ellison=E2=80=99s pitch because it was the opposite. He and his father woul=
d buy her studio and leverage the family=E2=80=99s wealth to, ultimately, t=
ry to save it.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p sty=
le=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">That informal covenant=E2=80=94one of ma=
ny, <em>many</em> odd aspects of the Paramount/Skydance transaction that un=
folded through most of a tumultuous 2024=E2=80=94was more appealing to Reds=
tone than might be expected. If she had simply chosen to auction off her fa=
mily=E2=80=99s
media assets one by one, few would have blamed her. As the controlling shar=
eholder of National Amusements Inc.=E2=80=94which in turn owns Paramount, w=
hich itself comprises everything from CBS to BET to Paramount+ to the studi=
o lot and the flowers on Michael Bay Avenue=E2=80=94that was her right, and=
 probably would have netted her more.=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"marg=
in:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">But she didn=E2=
